- [ ] Ensure the Apify dataset import handles posts with property names for url other than "url"
- [ ] Add filters to Apify dataset import to skip posts that don't contain text content
- [ ] use Mastra AI client SDK @mastra/client-js in `gtm-workers` to call the mastra-based gtm-ai service.
- [ ] posts from crawlers might not have a 'url' property. The value should always be present, but the property
might have a different name. We should handle this by potentially renaming properties after parsing. We should not
hash the entire object because properties like "number of likes" can change independent of the posts' contents.
- [ ] We should attempt to parse posts using the expected schema when importing the dataset in order to obtain the url
and post origination date. We should also filter posts by origination date to avoid importing old posts.
- [ ] Support graceful shutdown for workers
- [ ] Add separate package.json scripts for unit and integration test suites so that unit tests can run without infrastructure dependencies